courses.learning_outcomes:
The objectives of the course are, through the design, organization and implementation of a field study outside Hong Kong, to enable the students to:
- acquire awareness of, and an appreciation for, the diversity and complexity of the international business environment;
- understand the role of analysis of macro dimensions (cultural, demographic, economic, educational, environmental, legal, political, sociological and technological) in making global business decisions;
- review contemporary and relevant developments in the global or regional arena, and to explore the possible strategic alternatives to capitalize on changes in the global scenario;
- apply business/ management concepts and skills acquired during the EMBA program in a real-life global business context; and
- generate insightful and concrete business plans based on the research findings of the field study.
